The ‘Cyclic poets' were those epic poets, who probably aster the Iliad and the Odyssey had assumed their present form, wrote upon various legends, more or less closely connected with the Theban and Trojan wars. They did not, as has been erroneously supposed, intentionally write a cycle of poems; but the grammarians put together by their aid a cycle of legends.
